    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "MACRS depreciation for a 7-year property class, you say? Well, the formula is quite straightforward: \n\nMACRS Depreciation = (Cost of Asset - Residual Value) / Useful Life\n\nFor a 7-year property class, the useful life is 7 years. The residual value is the expected value of the asset at the end of its useful life. \n\nAs for the rate, it's 20% for the first year. You can use the following formula to calculate the depreciation for the first year:\n\nYear 1 Depreciation = Cost of Asset - Residual Value\n\nBut, if you don't know the residual value, you can use the 20% rate as a shortcut: \n\nYear 1 Depreciation = 20% of Cost of Asset\n\nFor example, let's say the cost of the equipment is $100,000. \n\nYear 1 Depreciation = 20% of $100,000 = $20,000\n\nYou can then subtract this amount from the cost to find the residual value. \n\nResidual Value = Cost of Asset - Year 1 Depreciation = $100,000 - $20,000 = $80,000\n\nNow, you can",
